"guid":"_79Y3SmeTxuNANxOml8y0w","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"Enfermedad diseminada → >90% mortalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"194","text":"Extension intracraneal → >80%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"194","text":"Neutropenia persistente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"194","text":"Retraso en inicio de tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"194","text":"Forma pulmonar bilateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"194","text":"Mucormicosis por Cunninghamella → mas letal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"201","parent":"192","text":"Factores de mejor\\Npronostico","guid":"OcF7t5Uf57_tS6cjcorY_g","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"Forma cutanea localizada → ~15-30%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"201","text":"Diagnostico precoz + cirugia temprana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"201","text":"Resolucion del factor predisponente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"201","text":"Forma rinocerebral sin extension SNC → ~25-40%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"206","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones\\Ngeriatricas","guid":"sjkmlY4xureSYyDnjm_zuQ","children":[{"id":"207","parent":"206","text":"Mayor prevalencia de DM tipo 2 y DM mal controlada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"206","text":"Polifarmacia → corticoides cronicos (EPOC, artritis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"206","text":"Inmunosenescencia → menor respuesta inmune innata","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"206","text":"Fragilidad → limita opciones quirurgicas agresivas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"206","text":"Nefrotoxicidad por AmB →\\NTFGe basal menor, mayor\\Nriesgo","guid":"Y4jDWTNPt1X7mFaqVo8Fjg","children":[{"id":"212","parent":"211","text":"Ajustar dosis segun CKD-EPI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"211","text":"Monitoreo estrecho K+, Mg2+, creatinina cada 24-48h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"214","parent":"206","text":"Interacciones farmacologicas de azoles → CYP3A4","guid":"","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"Anticoagulantes, estatinas, BCC, inmunosupresores","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"216","parent":"206","text":"Proporcionalidad\\Nterapeutica","guid":"LPj2VwF9ZtAiGIbEBrVSAQ","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"Evaluar estado funcional basal (Barthel, Lawton)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"216","text":"Discutir metas de cuidado con paciente/familia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"219","parent":"216","text":"Cirugia radical puede no ser apropiada en frágil severo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"220","parent":"206","text":"Valoracion geriatrica integral PREVIO a decision quirurgica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"221","parent":"0","text":"Mucormicosis asociada a\\NCOVID-19 (CAM)","guid":"ytdqCu6loLF_qJfZel3_uw","children":[{"id":"222","parent":"221","text":"Epidemia masiva en India 2021 → >45000 casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"221","text":"Factores: corticoides + hiperglicemia + linfopenia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"221","text":"Forma predominante: rinocerebral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"221","text":"DM no diagnosticada o mal controlada → factor principal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"221","text":"Uso excesivo de corticoides → dosis y duracion inadecuadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"221","text":"Oxigenoterapia con humidificadores contaminados → via aerea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"221","text":"Mortalidad CAM similar a mucormicosis clasica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"229","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClinicas","guid":"Ddw7ojtaQvAle2ej49syLg","children":[{"id":"230","parent":"229","text":"BDG NEGATIVO + IFI sospechada = PENSAR MUCORALES (no producen beta-glucano)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"229","text":"Escara negra nasal/palatina → mucormicosis hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"229","text":"Voriconazol NO cubre Mucorales → profilaxis con VRC puede seleccionar MCR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"229","text":"CAD + sinusitis necrotica = EMERGENCIA → iniciar L-AmB empirica inmediata","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"229","text":"Retraso >6 dias en inicio de antifungico duplica mortalidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"235","parent":"229","text":"Biopsia URGENTE ante sospecha → no esperar cultivos para iniciar tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"236","parent":"229","text":"Hifas anchas aseptadas a 90 grados → Mucorales (vs septadas 45 grados = Aspergillus)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"229","text":"Deferoxamina CONTRAINDICADA → actua como sideroforo para Mucorales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"229","text":"En geriatrico: evaluar proporcionalidad antes de cirugia radical","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"239","parent":"229","text":"Isavuconazol → alternativa oral razonable para step-down en AM fragil","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"240","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"241","parent":"240","text":"1. Kontoyiannis DP, Walsh TJ. Mucormycosis. N Engl J Med. 2026;394(7):684-698.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"240","text":"2. Alqarihi A, et al. Mucormycosis in 2023: an update on pathogenesis and management. Front Cell Infect Microbiol. 2023;13:1254919.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"240","text":"3. Liang M, et al. Epidemiology, pathogenesis, clinical characteristics, and treatment of mucormycosis. Ann Med. 2024;56(1):2396570.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"240","text":"4. Roland LT, et al. Diagnosis, Prognosticators, and Management of AIFS: Multidisciplinary Consensus Statement. Int Forum Allergy Rhinol. 2023;13(9):1615-1714.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"240","text":"5. Azar MM. A Diagnostic Approach to Fungal Pneumonia. CHEST. 2024;165(3):559-572.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"240","text":"6. Cornely OA, et al. Global guideline for the diagnosis and management of mucormycosis. Lancet Infect Dis. 2019;19(12):e405-e421.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"240","text":"7. Spellberg B, et al. Novel perspectives on mucormycosis. Clin Microbiol Rev. 2005;18(3):556-569.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":247,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Mucormicosis iPad","id":"map_821","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Mucormicosis iPad"}